UC Berkeley - Amyloid PET 6mm Res analysis

Source: R/data.R
UCBERKELEY_AMY_6MM.Rd

UC Berkeley - Amyloid PET 6mm Res analysis data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(UCBERKELEY_AMY_6MM)

Format

A data frame with 4127 observations and 344 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNIGO, ADNI4

  • LONIUID character LONI Image ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID (unique participant identifier that should be used to merge data) Range value: 21, ..., 10340

  • VISCODE character Visit code

  • SITEID numeric Site ID Range value: 2, ..., 941

  • PTID character ADNI Participant ID consisting of 3-digit "SITEID" and 4-digit "RID"

  • SCANDATE Date Scan acquisition date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • PROCESSDATE Date Date quantification pipeline was run Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • IMAGE_RESOLUTION character Spatial resolution in mm^3 FWHM of Step4 Preprocessed PET image. See UCBERKELEY PET 8mm-to-6mm Transformation Methods PDF on LONI for details. , with options: 6mm, 8mm

  • qc_flag numeric Range value: -2, ..., 2

  • TRACER character PET Radiotracer , with options: FBB, FBP

  • TRACER_SUVR_WARNING character Reminder of the incomparability of SUVRs from different tracers. See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF. , with options: USE CENTILOIDS (NOT SUVRs) TO COMPARE ACROSS TRACERS

  • AMYLOID_STATUS numeric Amyloid positivity determined by applying thresholds to cortical summary SUVR normalized by whole cerebellum; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 0, ..., 1

  • AMYLOID_STATUS_COMPOSITE_REF numeric Amyloid positivity determined by applying thresholds to cortical summary SUVR normalized by composite ref region; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 0, ..., 1

  • CENTILOIDS numeric Summary cortical SUVR normalized by whole cerebellum and transformed to Centiloids. All SUVRs in this file are normalized to the whole cerebellum unless otherwise noted. See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: -39, ..., 346

  • SUMMARY_SUVR numeric Summary cortical SUVR normalized by whole cerebellum. All SUVRs in this file are normalized to the whole cerebellum unless otherwise noted. See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 0.797, ..., 2.842

  • SUMMARY_VOLUME numeric Summary cortical ROI size in mm^3 Range value: 179914, ..., 423018

  • WHOLECEREBELLUM_SUVR numeric Reference region - mean SUVR of whole cerebellum. Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 1, ..., 1

  • WHOLECEREBELLUM_VOLUME numeric Reference region - volume of whole cerebellum. Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 85374, ..., 180735

  • COMPOSITE_REF_SUVR numeric Reference region - mean SUVR of composite ref region (avg of whole cerebellum, brainstem, eroded WM). Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 1.078, ..., 2.362

  • COMPOSITE_REF_VOLUME numeric Reference region - volume of composite ref region (avg of whole cerebellum, brainstem, eroded WM). Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 173936, ..., 502106

  • CEREBELLUM_CORTEX_SUVR numeric Reference region - mean SUVR of bilateral-cerebellum-cortex defined by Freesurfer (previously CEREBELLUMGREYMATTER_SUVR); See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 0.754, ..., 0.955

  • CEREBELLUM_CORTEX_VOLUME numeric Reference region - volume of bilateral-cerebellum-cortex defined by Freesurfer (previously CEREBELLUMGREYMATTER_VOLUME); See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 68832, ..., 142592

  • ERODED_SUBCORTICALWM_SUVR numeric Reference region - mean SUVR of eroded subcortical white matter. Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 1.192, ..., 3.97

  • ERODED_SUBCORTICALWM_VOLUME numeric Reference region - volume of eroded subcortical white matter. Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 55673, ..., 313526

  • BRAINSTEM_SUVR numeric Reference region - mean SUVR of brainstem. Regions defined by Freesurfer; See UCBERKELEY Amyloid Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 1.043, ..., 2.116

  • BRAINSTEM_VOLUME numeric brain-stem ROI size in mm^3 Range value: 13764, ..., 31506
